cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper focuses on visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves learning feature embeddings in an end-to-end way using deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of shrinkage loss, which is a common loss function in multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Finally, the proposed tracker is designed to run in real-time, which is a key requirement in robotics (cs.RO) applications.
